ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Must get to know labs better with this course.
There is no choice, they have to take it.

Yes I would recommend lab rotations to other students. The lab rotations provide a good opportunity to explore different laboratory environments and research, while also providing the opportunity to learn new lab techniques.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: Indispensable in giving you a flavor for what you'll be doing for the remaining 5 years!
I found the lab I'm going to join!
It played an important part of my thesis decision making.
Gave me excellent insight into the work done here at Yale and an opportunity to learn many useful techniques.

This course deepened my knowledge of various fields of research and contributed to my profession by allowing me to explore different labs and research options before selecting a lab in which I would ultimately perform my dissertation research.
